{{Infobox company | name = Bugsense | type = [[Private Company]] | foundation = 2011 | founder = Jon Vlachogiannis, Panayiotis Papadopoulos | location = [[Athens]], [[Greece]] | industry = [[Mobile application development]] | homepage = {{URL|http://www.bugsense.com}} }} '''''Bugsense''''' is a [[crash reporter]] for mobile phones. It collects and analyzes crash reports, performance and quality of applications on mobiles,<ref>Albright, S. (2012, March 13). ''[http://phandroid.com/2012/03/13/bugsense-must-have-tool-for-android-developers/ Bugsense: Must Have Tool For Android Developers.]'' at PB Android. Retrieved January 2, 2014.</ref> which forwards them to the creators of those applications to act on them. Supported platforms include Android, [[iOS]], [[Windows Phone 7]], [[Windows Phone]], [[Windows 8]] and [[HTML 5]].<ref>Sæther, P. O. (n.d.). ''[http://breathingtech.com/2012/live-crash-reports-for-your-apps-using-bugsense/ Live crash reports for your apps using BugSense]'' at Breathing Tech. Retrieved January 2, 2014.</ref>
==History== The company was founded in 2011 by [https://www.linkedin.com/in/johnvlachoyiannis Jon Vlachogiannis] and Panayiotis Papadopoulos.<ref name="Crunch">Raan, J. (2013, January 13).''[http://www.crunchbase.com/company/bugsense Crunchbase.com]'' at [[Crunchbase]]. Retrieved January 2, 2014.</ref> Initial funds ($100.000)<ref name="Crunch" /> were acquired by Silicon Valley Greek Seed Funding Group.<ref>N,E. (2012, April 10). ''[http://colabworkspace.com/2012/04/fighting-bugs-of-all-kinds-an-interview-with-bugsense-and-its-journey-to-success/ Fighting bugs of all kinds. An interview with bugsense and its journey to success.] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106033149/http://colabworkspace.com/2012/04/fighting-bugs-of-all-kinds-an-interview-with-bugsense-and-its-journey-to-success/ |date=January 6, 2014 }}'' Retrieved January 2, 2014.</ref> Bugsense expanded to supporting more than 30000 developers and companies, including [[Samsung]], [[Soundcloud]], and [[Trulia]]<ref>''[https://angel.co/bugsense Angel.co]'' Retrieved January 2, 2014.</ref> and has a market share of 3.43% of all apps.<ref>(2014, January 5). ''[http://www.appbrain.com/stats/libraries/details/bugsense/bugsense Appbrain.com]'' Retrieved January 5, 2014</ref> In September 2013, Bugsense was acquired by [[Splunk]].<ref>(2013, September 16). Press Release''[https://www.wsj.com/article/PR-CO-20130916-908332.html The Wall Street Journal]'' at [[Wall Street Journal]] Retrieved January 2, 2014</ref>
