'''Digital reproduction''' is one form of data [[reproduction]] which is based on the [[Digital data|digital]] data model. The advantage of digital reproduction of data over analogue reproduction is its [[lossless]] quality. Reproducing analogue data is inherently [[lossy]], because every (electronic) component involved in any analogue reproduction process can introduce noise to the final result.

Compare [[analogue processing]] to [[digital processing]].

