{{Infobox company | name = TutorVista Global Pvt. Ltd | logo = Tutorvista.png | type = [[Private company|Private]] | industry = [[Internet]], [[e-learning]], [[Education]], [[Tutoring]] | foundation = November 2005 | founder = Krishnan Ganesh and Meena Ganesh | location_city = Bangalore, Karnataka | products = [[Online tutoring]] [[Homework help]] | location_country = [[India]] | homepage = <!-- {{URL|http://www.tutorvista.com}} --> }} '''TutorVista Global Private Limited''' (acquired by BYJUs) is an educational organisation that specializes in [[online tutoring]] majorly in the US. The website and its content are provided mainly in English. It relies on a combination of voice over Internet Protocol ([[Voice over IP|VoIP]]) telephony, session recording, [[instant messaging]], file sharing and an interactive whiteboard<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.cnet.com/2010-1038-6126868.html|title=Outsourced tutors just an ocean away - CNET News|date=2012-07-13|work=archive.is|access-date=2017-10-06|deadurl=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120713214526/http://news.cnet.com/2010-1038-6126868.html|archivedate=13 July 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref>. The company mainly provides academic help by paid subscription to students in subjects such as English, Mathematics, Statistics and Science<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=i0_uAAAAMAAJ|title=Time|last=Luce|first=Henry Robinson|date=2006|publisher=Time Incorporated|language=en}}</ref>.
TutorVista’s operations are entirely located in India, but most of its market is abroad<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://iis-db.stanford.edu/evnts/4587/Stanford.pdf|title=The Evolving Indian Offshore Services Environment: Greater Breadth, Depth, and Scope|last=|first=|date=|website=iis-db.stanford.edu|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070611031201/http://iis-db.stanford.edu/evnts/4587/Stanford.pdf|archive-date=2007-06-11|dead-url=yes|access-date=}}</ref>. TutorVista’s online tutorial platform connects students with about 2,000 teachers across India, United States, UK, Australia, China, Middle East and South East Asia<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/special/byjus-acquires-tutorvista-and-edurite-from-pearson/47449/1|title=Byju's acquires TutorVista and Edurite from Pearson {{!}} Forbes India|website=Forbes India|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-06}}</ref>. TutorVista is reachable through computers, tablets, and mobile phones.
==History== TutorVista was founded in the year 2005 by the duo Krishnan Ganesh and Meena Ganesh<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VbRIAAAAYAAJ|title=Business India|date=2005|publisher=A. H. Advani|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vccircle.com/news/healthcare-services/2013/07/18/tutorvista-founders-krishnan-meena-ganesh-venture-healthcare|title=TutorVista founders Krishnan & Meena Ganesh venture into healthcare services; close to raising $10M|date=2014-04-23|work=VCCircle|access-date=2017-10-06|language=en-US}}</ref> with over years of experience in e-learning. Other formation contributors included Srinivas Anumolu, Louise Kumar, and Ravi Kannan. In 2006, [[Sequoia Capital]] India and [[Lightspeed Venture Partners|Light speed Venture Partners]] invested more than $10 million in TutorVista.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/banking/finance/sequoia-to-put-in-3-million-in-tutorvista/articleshow/856691.cms?intenttarget=no|title=Sequoia to put in $3 million in TutorVista|last=M|first=Thanuja B.|date=2006-12-20|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2017-10-06}}</ref>
The company expanded with the acquisition of Edurite, an educational firm in 2007<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/todays-paper/tp-info-tech/tutorvista-buys-edurite-technologies/article1675509.ece|title=TutorVista buys Edurite Technologies|date=2007-11-23|work=The Hindu Business Line|access-date=2017-10-06|language=en}}</ref> and a partnership with [[American Book Company (1996)|American Book Company]] in 2009.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20070417005391/en/TutorVista-American-Book-Company-Link-Provide-Free|title=TutorVista and American Book Company Link to Provide Free Tutoring for Improved Test Scores|website=www.businesswire.com|language=en|access-date=2017-10-06}}</ref> In 2011, [[Pearson plc|Pearson]] increased a smaller stake to a 76% majority stake in TutorVista for $127 million<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2011/jan/18/pearson-tutorvista-india|title=Pearson buys controlling stake in TutorVista for $127m|last=Sweney|first=Mark|date=2011-01-18|work=The Guardian|access-date=2017-10-06|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> and fully acquired it by buying the remaining 20% stake in 2013. At this point, Krishnan Ganesh and Meena Ganesh stepped down from all management roles in the Bangalore-based company and Srikanth Iyer was appointed the new CEO.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/pearson-ups-stake-in-tutorvista-to-own-100-113022400239_1.html|title=Pearson ups stake in TutorVista to own 100%|last=Mitra|first=Sounak|date=2013-02-24|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2017-10-06}}</ref>
== Acquisitions and investments == * TutorVista had acquired Edurite, an education solutions provider, in 2007. * Pearson acquired a 17% stake in TutorVista from Bengaluru-based entrepreneur-investor couple K Ganesh and Meena Ganesh in 2009. * In January 2011, it purchased another 59% holding for Rs 577 crore before increasing its controlling stake to 80% shortly after. * Two years later, Pearson acquired the remaining 20%. * TutorVista, founded by serial entrepreneur K Ganesh in 2005, was bought by Pearson in a multi-million (around Rs. 1000 crore) deal across several years which was completed in 2013. * Bengaluru-based edutech company Byju’s has acquired the online education ventures of TutorVista and Edurite from the world’s biggest learning company Pearson in June 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/byjus-acquires-tutorvista-and-edurite/articleshow/59427281.cms|title=Byju's acquires TutorVista, Edurite from Pearson|last=Vignesh|first=J.|date=2017-07-03|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2017-10-06}}</ref>
==Criticism== ''[[The Economist]]'' has suggested that building trust for an unknown Indian brand was the biggest difficulty faced by the company.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.economist.com/node/9358954 | work=[[The Economist]] | title=The outsourcerer | date=21 June 2007}}</ref> There have also been several protests in the United States against those organizations that do not allow face-to-face and personalized tutoring. Officials and parents from both local and national bodies have mixed reactions regarding the ethical and practical implications of this trend.<ref>{{cite news|title=Online Tutoring and the Offshoring of Education| url=http://tcc.kcc.hawaii.edu/previous/TCC%202007/ciano.pdf }}</ref> In the UK it is estimated that 1 in 4 students is now tutored outside school, with offshore tutoring companies increasingly entering the market.<ref>{{cite news|title=Facebook generation fuels boom in online tutors | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/education/educationnews/9029841/Facebook-generation-fuels-boom-in-online-tutors.html | location=London | work=The Daily Telegraph | first=Julie | last=Henry | date=22 January 2012}}</ref>
