{{Infobox company | name = Wahoo Fitness, LLC | logo = | type = [[Private company]]| | industry = [[Technology]] | products = [[Bicycle trainer]], [[Heart rate monitor]], [[Cycling computer]], Cycling sensor | foundation = [[Atlanta|Atlanta, Georgia]], U.S. (2010) | founder = Chip Hawkins| | hq_location_city = Atlanta | hq_location_country = United States | area_served = Worldwide | num_employees = 80-100 | num_employees_year = 2017 | website = <!-- {{www.wahoofitness.com/|http://www.wahoofitness.com/}} --> }}
'''Wahoo Fitness''' is a fitness technology company based in [[Atlanta, Georgia]].<ref name="dcr">{{cite web|url=http://www.dcrainmaker.com/2014/08/behind-scenes-fitness.html|title=Behind the Scenes at Wahoo Fitness HQ|work=[[DC Rainmaker]]|accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref> Its CEO is Chip Hawkins.
As of August 2014 Wahoo Fitness had 35 employees.<ref name="dcr"/>
Wahoo is the official indoor trainer of [[Team Sky]], with athletes including [[Chris Froome]] as users of their KICKR trainer.<ref name="dcr"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.pezcyclingnews.com/newswire/team-sky-renews-wahoo-fitness-as-official-indoor-trainer-supplier-for-the-2015-season/|title=Team Sky Renews Wahoo Fitness as Official Indoor Trainer Supplier for the 2015 Season|work=PEZ Cycling News|accessdate=16 September 2015}}</ref> ==Products== Wahoo's most popular product is the GPS bike computer Elemnt Bolt. It is the successor of the Elemnt, having the same functionality but the Elemnt has a bigger screen size. Wahoo has several types of bike trainers, called Kickr. Their heart rates monitors are Tickr and Tickr X.
